nodes.title: STEP 1
widgets_values:
Select an image above and mask the area you want to modify

Set the desired resolution next in the Resize Image node from Mixlab. SDXL prefers 1024x1024 while SD 1.5 prefers a 512x512 image size. You can use different sizes as long as they are withing the SDXL/SD1.5 trained dataset. Dimensions should be divisible by 64

Once your selection is made, the Text Mask Overlay node will use the masked area as a bounding box to fit the character(s) selected and create an image mask. You can run just the preview nodes to see what your font and character selection will be before you Queue the Prompt. To run just the preview nodes, use the "rgthree" custom nodes extension which give you a right-click context option to just execute up to the selected node.

nodes.title: STEP 3
widgets_values:
Characters and Fonts to use for interesting results

Fonts: impact.ttf, DejaVBuSans-Bold.ttf

malgunbb.ttf and PangMenZhengDow-Cu-6.0.ttf are great for Asian Characters and I have included them with the node. They are in the "Node Folder" drop down above which pulls them from ./ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ComfyUI_YFG_Comical/fonts/

Asian character sets are great for artistic expression. Feel free to use one of more of these

The imgBB to Image node helps download the image from the service.

If you have the "rgthree" custom nodes installed, right-click on the imgBB to Image node above and execute to download the image. You can then move it to your preferred location or use it directly in your workflow. You just have to connect the mask or image output to the right inputs.
